flowRoot.flowPara: It follows from enzymology that the substance consumption rate is not linearly proportional to the substance concentration s. Above a given value of concentration, consumption does not increase, creating an assymptote in the consumption response. The functional form of this relation depends on the maximum uptake rate and the saturation constant Ks. See Panikov, N. S. (2016). Kinetics of microbial processes.

The chemotatic response of microorganisms is also not a linear function of substance gradient. It presents a maximum sensitivity above which an increase in substance concentration does not reflect on increased chemotatic response. See Cremer, J. et al. (2019). Chemotaxis as a navigation strategy to boost range expansion. and Fu, X. et al. Spatial self-organization resolves conflicts between individuality and collective migration. (2018).
